        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 1:59AM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 158 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Redbank Spring Campground, or 13 miles northeast of Newcastle, moving
east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rapid City, Sturgis, southwestern Rapid Valley, Summerset, Black
Hawk, Johnson Siding, Nemo, Piedmont, Hisega, Silver City, Rochford,
Flag Mountain, Mystic, Moon, Brownsville, Four Corners, Galena,
Deerfield, Tilford, and Deerfield Reservoir.

This includes Interstate 90 in South Dakota between Mile Markers 32
and 61.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
